{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24},"timestamp":1777486099,"command":"bash demo/redirect-demo.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.038, "o", "\u001b[1;32m✓ git-prism 0.6.0\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;34m║\u001b[0m  \u001b[1;36mSegment 1: The training problem\u001b[0m        \u001b[1;34m║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;34m╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[2m# git-prism is registered as an MCP server. Five structured tools.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m# But Claude was trained on millions of git commands.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m# That muscle memory does not go away just because an MCP server is installed.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[16.408, "o", "\u001b[2m# Claude reaches for git diff — exactly as its training taught it.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ \u001b[0m"]
[0.020, "o", "git "]
[0.191, "o", "diff"]
[0.091, "o", " HEA"]
[0.095, "o", "D~1."]
[0.096, "o", ".HEA"]
[0.094, "o", "D"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.329, "o", "diff --git a/demo/redirect-narration.md b/demo/redirect-narration.md\r\nindex e97b25d..11fc740 100644\r\n--- a/demo/redirect-narration.md\r\n+++ b/demo/redirect-narration.md\r\n@@ -4,31 +4,31 @@\r\n      Segment names map 1-to-1 to sleep-calibrated sections in demo/redirect-demo.sh. -->\r\n \r\n <!-- SEGMENT: problem_intro -->\r\n-I've got a notes file in a git repository here — tracked, committed, under version control. Now watch what happens when an agent runs an unguarded bash redirect.\r\n+Here is a git repository with a notes file containing research I want to keep. Under version control, tracked, committed. Now watch what happens when an agent runs an unguarded bash redirect.\r\n \r\n <!-- SEGMENT: problem_clobber -->\r\n-The file is gone. One redirect operator, no confirmation, no diff, no way back. The original content is overwritten and git history cannot help because the change was never staged. That's the problem git-prism v 0.7.0 solves.\r\n+The file is gone. One bash redirect — no diff, no prompt, no recovery path. Th"]
[0.000, "o", "e original content is overwritten and git history can not help because the change never staged. This is the problem git-prism v 0.7.0 solves.\r\n \r\n <!-- SEGMENT: hook_intro -->\r\n-git-prism ships a Claude Code PreToolUse hook that intercepts every Bash tool call before it runs. It reads the command from standard input and returns one of three decisions: block it, advise against it, or pass through silently.\r\n+git-prism ships a Claude Code PreToolUse hook that intercepts every Bash tool call before it runs. It reads the command as JSON on stdin and returns one of three decisions: block it, advise against it, or pass through silently.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", " \r\n <!-- SEGMENT: hook_block -->\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "-A command like gh pr diff gets blocked outright — exit code 2 stops the tool call cold. Raw patch text isn't something an agent can act on reliably, so the hook prevents it entirely.\r\n+A command like g-h p-r diff gets blocked outright — exit code 2 stops the tool call cold. Raw patch text is not something an agent can act on reliably, so the hook prevents it entirely.\r\n \r\n <!-- SEGMENT: hook_advisory -->\r\n-git diff between refs gets an advisory instead. The hook lets it through — exit code zero, no interruption — but adds a suggestion in the output: use get change manifest instead, which returns structured data.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[2m  ... (truncated for demo) ...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# Hunk headers, plus and minus prefixes — for humans, not agents.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m# Five structured tools, one tool call away. Unused.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[16.906, "o", "\u001b[1;34m╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;34m║\u001b[0m  \u001b[1;36mSegment 2: How the hook works\u001b[0m          \u001b[1;34m║\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m# The hook is a Claude Code PreToolUse program. It reads a JSON\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m# payload on stdin and decides via exit code: 0 allow, 0+JSON\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m# advisory, 2 block.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;33m# Block: gh pr diff returns raw text — exit 2 stops it cold.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$ \u001b[0m"]
[0.015, "o", "echo"]
[0.186, "o", " {.."]
[0.091, "o", ".gh "]
[0.095, "o", "pr d"]
[0.094, "o", "iff "]
[0.094, "o", "123."]
[0.093, "o", "..} "]
[0.093, "o", "| py"]
[0.093, "o", "thon"]
[0.094, "o", "3 ho"]
[0.091, "o", "oks/"]
[0.095, "o", "bash"]
[0.093, "o", "_red"]
[0.091, "o", "irec"]
[0.185, "o", "t_ho"]
[0.095, "o", "ok.p"]
[0.091, "o", "y"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.558, "o", "git-prism: gh pr diff returns raw text. Use git-prism instead:\r\n  get_change_manifest(repo_path, base_ref, head_ref, include_function_analysis=true)\r\nStructured per-function change data — same info, no diff noise.\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1;31mexit code: 2\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[9.208, "o", "\u001b[1;33m# Advisory: git diff gets a nudge toward get_change_manifest — exit 0.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$ \u001b[0m"]
[0.014, "o", "echo"]
[0.189, "o", " {.."]
[0.092, "o", ".git"]
[0.096, "o", " dif"]
[0.095, "o", "f ma"]
[0.093, "o", "in.."]
[0.095, "o", "HEAD"]
[0.095, "o", "...}"]
[0.095, "o", " | p"]
[0.090, "o", "ytho"]
[0.092, "o", "n3 h"]
[0.092, "o", "ooks"]
[0.095, "o", "/bas"]
[0.094, "o", "h_re"]
[0.095, "o", "dire"]
[0.095, "o", "ct_h"]
[0.182, "o", "ook."]
[0.093, "o", "py"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.560, "o", "{\"hookSpecificOutput\": {\"hookEventName\": \"PreToolUse\", \"permissionDecision\": \"allow\", \"additionalContext\": \"git diff between refs returns raw text. git-prism alternative:\\n  get_change_manifest(repo_path, base_ref, head_ref, include_function_analysis=true)\\nReturns structured per-file change data with function-level semantic analysis.\\n\\nYou ran: git diff main..HEAD\"}}\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1;32mexit code: 0\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[10.806, "o", "\u001b[1;33m# Silent: a benign command — no output, exit 0.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ \u001b[0m"]
